## `update_mode_uid_gid(conn, inode, *, mode=None, uid=None, gid=None, ctime_ns)`
<!-- checksum: nodes-7 -->

### Purpose
Partial update of ownership/mode. Always bumps `ctime_ns` — per POSIX, any metadata change bumps ctime.

### Postconditions
- Only the provided fields are changed.
- `ctime_ns` is set to the provided value.

### Implementation Notes

```python
def update_mode_uid_gid(conn, inode, *, mode=None, uid=None, gid=None, ctime_ns):
    fields = []
    values = []
    if mode is not None:
        fields.append("mode = ?"); values.append(mode)
    if uid is not None:
        fields.append("uid = ?"); values.append(uid)
    if gid is not None:
        fields.append("gid = ?"); values.append(gid)
    fields.append("ctime_ns = ?"); values.append(ctime_ns)
    values.append(inode)
    conn.execute(f"UPDATE nodes SET {', '.join(fields)} WHERE inode = ?",
                 tuple(values))
```

### Test Strategy
- `test_durability.test_reopen_preserves_mode_uid_gid`.

